ps://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m902a3f1.gif","alt":"The figure shows the percentage of visits for influenza-like illness (ILI) reported by the U.S. Outpatient Influenza-like Illness Surveillance Network (ILINet), by surveillance week in the United States for the 2006-07, 2007-08, 2008-09, and 2009-10 influenza seasons. In the week ending October 24, 2009, the weekly percentage of outpatient visits for ILI reported by the U.S. Outpatient ILINet reached 7.7%, the highest level to date this influenza season and a level higher than the three preceding seasons. After peaking, the ILI level decreased to 1.9% in the week ending January 9, 2010.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":699,"renderedHeight":243,"naturalWidth":699,"naturalHeight":243,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 593 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":18919},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m902a3f2.gif","alt":"The figure shows the number of 2009-10 laboratory-confirmed influenza-associated hospitalizations and cumulative hospitalization rates per 10,000 population, by age group and surveillance week from Emerging Infections Program (EIP), and new sites for the 2006-07, 2007-08, 2008-09,† and 2009-10§ influenza seasons. As of January 9, 2010, cumulative rates of laboratory-confirmed influenza-associated hospitalizations reported for children aged 0-4 years were 5.9 per 10,000 population by EIP and 9.7 per 10,000 population by the new sites.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":463,"renderedHeight":812,"naturalWidth":463,"naturalHeight":812,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 539 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":26074},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m902a3f2.gif","alt":"The figure shows the percentage of all deaths attributed to pneumonia and influenza (P&I), by surveillance week and year for 122 U.S. cities from 2006-2010 from the Mortality Reporting System. For the week ending January 9, pneumonia or influenza was reported as an underlying or contributing cause of death for 7.3% of all deaths reported through the 122 Cities Mortality Reporting System, below the week-specific epidemic threshold of 7.6%.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":463,"renderedHeight":812,"naturalWidth":463,"naturalHeight":812,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 442 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":26074},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m902a3f4.gif","alt":"The figure shows the number of influenza-associated pediatric deaths, by week of death in the United States for the 2006-07, 2007-08, 2008-09, and 2009-10 influenza seasons. CDC has received 236 reports of pediatric deaths associated with laboratory-confirmed influenza infection that occurred and were reporting since August 30, 2009.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":692,"renderedHeight":354,"naturalWidth":692,"naturalHeight":354,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 335 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":33890},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_pdf.gif","alt":"Adobe PDF file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":6058},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_word.gif","alt":"Microsoft Word file","hasAlt":tr